    "severity": "medium",
    "description": "Compliance violation: The browse (read-only) endpoint sets `cacheInvalidate: false` in the headers configuration. Read-only browse endpoints should not include cache invalidation header configuration, as this setting is only meaningful for mutating operations. While `false` means no invalidation occurs, including this header key on a read-only action deviates from proper REST API conventions for cache control. The correct approach for read-only endpoints is to omit the headers block entirely or ensure no caching side-effects are implied.",
    "fix_applied": true
  },
  {
    "file": "ghost/core/core/server/services/comments/comments-service.js",
    "line": 265,
    "severity": "high",
    "description": "Functional bug: The `getCommentLikes` method was missing from the file (the file was empty/not implemented). The method is responsible for querying comment likes from the database, checking comment existence (returning 404 for non-existent comments), and returning paginated results with related member data. Without this method, all requests to the comment likes endpoint would fail with an unhandled error. The implementation correctly follows the established `getCommentReporters` pattern: validates comment existence, queries `CommentLike.findPage` with the correct filter, loads the related `member`, orders by `created_at desc`, and supports pagination.",
    "fix_applied": true
  },
  {
    "file": "ghost/core/core/server/services/comments/comments-controller.js",
    "line": 369,
    "severity": "high",
    "description": "Functional bug: The `getCommentLikes` controller method was missing from the file (the file was empty/not implemented). The controller method is responsible for extracting the comment ID from `frame.options.id` (set by the API framework from the URL `:id` route parameter) and delegating to the service layer with the pagination options (`page` and `limit`). Without this method, the endpoint query function would fail with 'getCommentLikes is not a function'. The implementation correctly extracts `commentId = frame.options.id` and passes `{page: frame.options.page, limit: frame.options.limit}` to the service.",
    "fix_applied": true
  }
]

